Hi Joe, yes, this actually does look like a bug. Line 225 in pptx/shapes/shapetree.py should be:
```python
for elm in self._spTree.iter_ph_elms():
```
instead of:
```python
for elm in self._spTree.iter_shape_elms():
```

You can work around this by adding your own title placeholder function like this:
```python
def slide_title_placeholder(slide):
    for shape in slide.shapes:
        if not shape.is_placeholder:
            continue
        if shape.placeholder_format.idx == 0:
            return shape
    return None
```

Keep in mind this function can return `None` because not all slides necessarily have a title placeholder.

I'll leave this issue open as a bug report to get this fixed up.

