@daveFNbuck thanks for the feedback. Do you think updating the docstring would be sufficient to highlight the concerns about depending on dynamic default tasks?

Seems like in general though it seems risky to depend on defaults throughout your graph if you're expecting consistent values? For example if I were running the task from 2 different workers, wouldn't I have a similar problem where the two workers, running the same task, might have some dependent tasks that initialized to a different default value?

Also, can you clarify what the suggested test should cover? That if the default_callable changes between two task instantiations, you won't get the cached version? If you manually specify the parameter or default_callable doesn't change, though, you'd still get the cached version?

I did fix the code for the model which has  TransformationComp_Rotation, TransformationComp_Scaling, TransformationComp_GeometricScaling, TransformationComp_Translation, TransformationComp_GeometricRotation and TransformationComp_GeometricTranslation. But for the case where model needs "ComplexTransformationChain", I could not fix the issue. I am not understanding the logic which are using for this case.
Basically I am storing geometric transform of each node in separate matrix, so when we calculate final transform for each node, I am multiplying current node's transform with the inverse of parent's geometric transform. 
here is the code:

	void TransformNodes(aiNode *CurrentNode)
	{
		ai_assert(CurrentNode);

		if(CurrentNode->mParent) {
			aiMatrix4x4 parentGeomTransform=CurrentNode->mParent->mGeomTransformation;
			parentGeomTransform= parentGeomTransform.Inverse();			
			CurrentNode->mTransformation=parentGeomTransform * CurrentNode->mTransformation;
			
			
		}
		
		for(int i=0;i<CurrentNode->mNumChildren;i++)
			TransformNodes(CurrentNode->mChildren[i]);		

	}

I am calling above function in the end.

