Hi @tufeixp, 
This is a only the first drop of the Unity integration with the SDK.
At the moment the `RealSenseDevice` script exposes the Options so that you can set some option across all sensors before initialization. In the future we have plans to provide a customized Inspector which could answer your requirements.
In the meanwhile, since the `RealSenseDevice` is a singleton you can use your own custom script to control the options in runtime:
```c#
foreach (var sensor in RealSenseDevice.Instance.ActiveProfile.Device.Sensors)
{
    foreach (var option in sensor.Options)
    {
        //Edit option
    }
}
```

